mething\");\n+            }\n         }};\n     }\n     b!();"}, {"sha": "68a3c81b6a804e7f25a23e454a171b7ef494c401", "filename": "tests/ui/item_after_statement.stderr", "status": "modified", "additions": 14, "deletions": 1, "changes": 15, "blob_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/32e2021b75f5bb5c83bf753de76ec9ed499d12cc/tests%2Fui%2Fitem_after_statement.stderr", "raw_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/raw/32e2021b75f5bb5c83bf753de76ec9ed499d12cc/tests%2Fui%2Fitem_after_statement.stderr", "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/contents/tests%2Fui%2Fitem_after_statement.stderr?ref=32e2021b75f5bb5c83bf753de76ec9ed499d12cc", "patch": "@@ -16,5 +16,18 @@ LL | |         println!(\"foo\");\n LL | |     }\n    | |_____^\n \n-error: aborting due to 2 previous errors\n+error: adding items after statements is confusing, since items exist from the start of the scope\n+  --> $DIR/item_after_statement.rs:32:13\n+   |\n+LL | /             fn say_something() {\n+LL | |                 println!(\"something\");\n+LL | |             }\n+   | |_____________^\n+...\n+LL |       b!();\n+   |       ----- in this macro invocation\n+   |\n+   = note: this error originates in a macro (in Nightly builds, run with -Z macro-backtrace for more info)\n+\n+error: aborting due to 3 previous errors\n "}]}